The dapper style of the roaring twenties has returned, with a little help from Baz Luhrmann's The Great Gatsby, and it seems men can be just as inspired as women.

Since Leonardo DiCaprio appeared in the character of Jay Gatsby showcasing an ultra-styled, slicked back hair style epitomising the polished 1920s style, one high-street pharmacy has seen sales of men’s hair pomade, wax and gel soar.

Sales of VO5 Extreme Style Grooming Hair Pomade have almost doubled, while Fudge Urban Matte Wax has seen sales rise 25 per cent when compared the same time in 2012 at Superdrug.

