Sales of Just For Men hair colorant have also benefited from the Gatsby effect with sales rising by a third as men rush out to emulate the film's super dapper stars.

Celebrities have also fallen for Gatsby’s slicked back style with stars such as David Beckham and Daniel Radcliffe choosing groomed retro styles.

And it’s not just men who are inspired by Gatsby, sales of self-grip small and medium hair rollers are up 24 per cent at teh same retailers as women aim for the finger-curled glamour of Daisy Buchanan played by Carey Mulligan.

Sarah Sharp, Senior Buyer of Hair at the high-street store said: 'Our customers love to follow the latest trends and The Great Gatsby is proving to be a huge inspiration for both men and women.

